# SHAREHOLDERS' AGREEMENT

**DATE:** {{date}}

**PARTIES:**

{{#shareholders}}
({{@index_plus_1}}) **{{name}}** of {{address}} ("**{{name_short}}**")
{{/shareholders}}

(together the "**Shareholders**" and each a "**Shareholder**")

**RELATING TO:**

**{{company_name}}**, a company incorporated in {{company_jurisdiction}} (the "**Company**")

3.1 **Board Size**: The Board shall consist of {{board_size}} Directors (or such other number as the Shareholders may agree in writing).

3.2 **Board Appointments**: The composition of the Board shall be as follows:

{{#shareholders}}
{{#if board_seats}}
   - **{{name}}** shall be entitled to appoint {{board_seats}} Director(s)
{{/if}}
{{/shareholders}}

3.3 **Appointment and Removal**:

   (a) Each Shareholder entitled to appoint a Director may do so by written notice to the Company and may remove and replace any Director so appointed at any time.

   (b) Appointor Shareholders shall procure that their appointed Directors attend all Board meetings and act in the best interests of the Company.

   (c) If an appointed Director resigns, is removed, or is otherwise unable to act, the appointing Shareholder shall appoint a replacement within [30 days].

3.4 **Board Observers**:

{{#shareholders}}
{{#if observer_rights}}
   (a) **{{name}}** shall be entitled to appoint one observer to attend Board meetings (without voting rights).
{{/if}}
{{/shareholders}}

   (b) Observers shall be entitled to receive all Board papers and information provided to Directors and to attend and speak at Board meetings, but shall not vote.

   (c) Observers shall owe the same duties of confidentiality as Directors.

3.5 **Board Meetings**:

   (a) The Board shall meet at least [quarterly / monthly].

   (b) Notice of meetings shall be given to all Directors and observers at least [7 days] in advance (or [48 hours] for urgent matters).

   (c) The quorum for Board meetings shall be [●] Directors (including at least one Founder Director and one Investor Director, if applicable).

   (d) Board decisions shall be made by [simple majority / unanimous consent], except for Reserved Matters which require the consent specified in Clause 5.

3.6 **Chairman**: The Board shall appoint a chairman who shall have a casting vote in the event of deadlock (unless otherwise agreed).

4.1 The Company shall not, without the prior written consent of [Shareholders holding at least {{reserved_matters_threshold}}% of the shares / the Majority Shareholders / specific Investor Shareholders]:

   (a) **Capital Structure**:

      (i) issue, allot, or grant rights to subscribe for any Securities (except pursuant to employee share option plans approved by Shareholders);

      (ii) redeem, purchase, or otherwise acquire any of its shares;

      (iii) reduce, sub-divide, consolidate, or reclassify the share capital;

      (iv) create any new class of shares or alter the rights attaching to any class;

   (b) **Corporate Transactions**:

      (i) enter into any merger, consolidation, or scheme of arrangement;

      (ii) dispose of the whole or any substantial part of its business or assets;

      (iii) acquire any business, company, or substantial assets;

      (iv) enter into any partnership or joint venture;

   (c) **Financial Matters**:

      (i) borrow or raise money, or incur debt (except trade credit in the ordinary course) in excess of [amount];

      (ii) give any guarantee, indemnity, or security over its assets (except in the ordinary course of business);

      (iii) make any loan (except to wholly-owned subsidiaries or employee loans in the ordinary course) in excess of [amount];

      (iv) approve the annual budget or any material departure from the approved budget;

      (v) declare or pay any dividend or other distribution;

   (d) **Operational Matters**:

      (i) materially change the nature or scope of the Company's business;

      (ii) cease or threaten to cease to carry on business;

      (iii) enter into any transaction with a Director, Shareholder, or their associates (except on arm's length terms);

      (iv) enter into any contract or commitment in excess of [amount] or outside the ordinary course of business;

      (v) create, acquire, or dispose of any material intellectual property;

   (e) **Personnel**:

      (i) appoint, remove, or materially vary the terms of employment of the Chief Executive Officer or other C-level executives;

      (ii) adopt or materially amend any employee share option or incentive plan;

      (iii) increase the aggregate remuneration of the senior management team by more than [●]% per annum;

   (f) **Governance and Legal**:

      (i) amend the Articles or any constitutional document of the Company or any subsidiary;

      (ii) pass any resolution for the winding up of the Company (except a solvent members' voluntary liquidation approved by Shareholders);

      (iii) present any petition for the bankruptcy or insolvency of the Company;

      (iv) bring, settle, or compromise any material litigation or arbitration (value exceeding [amount]);

      (v) change the Company's auditors or accounting reference date;

   (g) **IPO and Exit**:

      (i) make any application for admission of any Securities to any stock exchange or trading platform;

      (ii) approve the terms of any Exit Event.

4.2 The Shareholders undertake to exercise their voting rights to procure (so far as they are able by the exercise of such rights) that the Company complies with this Clause 4.

9.1 **Drag-Along Right**: If Shareholders holding at least {{drag_along_threshold}}% of the shares (the "**Dragging Shareholders**") approve a bona fide offer from a third party to:

   (a) purchase all of the shares in the Company; or

   (b) effect an Exit Event that would result in a change of control,

the Dragging Shareholders may require all other Shareholders (the "**Dragged Shareholders**") to participate in the transaction by giving written notice (a "**Drag Notice**").

9.2 **Drag Notice**: The Drag Notice shall specify:

   (a) the identity of the proposed purchaser;

   (b) the proposed purchase price and form of consideration;

   (c) the other material terms of the transaction;

   (d) the proposed completion date; and

   (e) the warranties, indemnities, and other obligations required of Shareholders.

9.3 **Obligations of Dragged Shareholders**: Each Dragged Shareholder shall:

   (a) sell all of their shares on the same terms as the Dragging Shareholders;

   (b) execute all transaction documents reasonably required;

   (c) give warranties and indemnities to the extent required, provided that:

      (i) Dragged Shareholders (other than Founders) shall only give warranties as to title, capacity, and authority;

      (ii) liability for business warranties shall be several (not joint) and allocated pro rata to consideration received;

      (iii) liability caps for Dragged Shareholders (other than Founders) shall not exceed the consideration they receive;

   (d) vote in favour of the transaction at any Shareholder meeting; and

   (e) take all other actions reasonably necessary to complete the transaction.

9.4 **Consideration**: Each Shareholder shall receive their pro rata share of the total consideration, calculated according to the liquidation waterfall in Clause 10.

9.5 **Founder Warranties**: Founder Shareholders acknowledge that they may be required to give comprehensive business warranties and indemnities, subject to customary limitations.

9.6 **Completion**: All Shareholders shall complete the sale simultaneously, and no Shareholder may withdraw once the drag-along process has been initiated.

12.1 **Price-Based Anti-Dilution**: If the Company issues Equity Securities at a price per share that is less than the [Series A] Conversion Price (a "**Down Round**"), the Conversion Price of the [Series A] Preference Shares shall be adjusted in accordance with this Clause 12.

{{#if_equals anti_dilution "weighted_average"}}
12.2 **Weighted Average Adjustment**: The adjusted Conversion Price shall be calculated using the following broad-based weighted average formula:

```
Adjusted Conversion Price = Original Conversion Price × 
  (A + B) / (A + C)

Where:
A = Number of shares outstanding immediately before the Down Round (fully diluted)
B = Consideration received / Original Conversion Price
C = Number of new shares issued in the Down Round
```
{{/if_equals}}

{{#if_equals anti_dilution "full_ratchet"}}
12.2 **Full Ratchet Adjustment**: The Conversion Price shall be reduced to the price per share at which new securities are issued in the Down Round.
{{/if_equals}}

{{#if_equals anti_dilution "none"}}
12.2 **No Anti-Dilution**: No anti-dilution adjustments shall apply.
{{/if_equals}}

12.3 **Exceptions**: Anti-dilution adjustments shall not apply to shares issued:

   (a) pursuant to employee share option plans;

   (b) as a dividend or distribution on Preference Shares;

   (c) in a transaction approved by [●]% of Preference Shareholders; or

   (d) [other agreed exceptions].

12.4 **Notice**: The Company shall notify all Preference Shareholders of any anti-dilution adjustment within [10 Business Days], providing full details of the calculation.

13.1 **Founder Warranties**: Each Founder warrants to each Investor (on a several basis) that:

   (a) they have full power and authority to enter into this Agreement;

   (b) they are the sole legal and beneficial owner of their shares;

   (c) their shares are fully paid and free from encumbrances;

   (d) the execution and performance of this Agreement does not breach any agreement to which they are party; and

   (e) [other customary founder warranties as appropriate].

13.2 **Company Warranties**: The Company warrants to each Investor that the share capital details in Schedule 1 are accurate and complete.

13.3 **Non-Compete** (Founders): Each Founder undertakes that, during their employment or engagement with the Company and for [12 months] thereafter, they shall not:

   (a) engage in or have any interest in any Competing Business;

   (b) solicit or entice away any employee, consultant, customer, or supplier of the Company; or

   (c) use or disclose any Confidential Information (as defined in their service agreement) of the Company.

13.4 **Full-Time Commitment** (Founders): Each Founder undertakes to devote substantially all of their business time and attention to the Company, except as otherwise agreed by the Board.

13.5 **Limitation**: The warranties in this Clause 13 are given on the date of this Agreement only and (except for warranties as to title and capacity) shall not be repeated.
